y_html": "<p>The defaults in layers such as conv and conv_transpose have the default activations as relu and the default initializer as xavier. From the paper <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/1502.01852v1.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://arxiv.org/pdf/1502.01852v1.pdf</a>, would this be the time to change the default initializer to use tf.contrib.layers.variance_scaling_initializer to account for the variance of the distributions being halved at each layer of activation?</p>\n<p>Andrej Karpathy has a lecture which shows the effects of this <a href=\"https://youtu.be/gYpoJMlgyXA?t=47m6s\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://youtu.be/gYpoJMlgyXA?t=47m6s</a></p>\n<p>edit:forgot to add time in the video</p>", "body_text": "The defaults in layers such as conv and conv_transpose have the default activations as relu and the default initializer as xavier. From the paper https://arxiv.org/pdf/1502.01852v1.pdf, would this be the time to change the default initializer to use tf.contrib.layers.variance_scaling_initializer to account for the variance of the distributions being halved at each layer of activation?\nAndrej Karpathy has a lecture which shows the effects of this https://youtu.be/gYpoJMlgyXA?t=47m6s\nedit:forgot to add time in the video", "body": "The defaults in layers such as conv and conv_transpose have the default activations as relu and the default initializer as xavier. From the paper https://arxiv.org/pdf/1502.01852v1.pdf, would this be the time to change the default initializer to use tf.contrib.layers.variance_scaling_initializer to account for the variance of the distributions being halved at each layer of activation?\r\n\r\nAndrej Karpathy has a lecture which shows the effects of this https://youtu.be/gYpoJMlgyXA?t=47m6s\r\n\r\nedit:forgot to add time in the video\r\n"}